    </nav>

    <header class="hero">
        <h1>Jailbreak</h1>
        <p>Intent vs. Behavior mobile malware analysis using Multimodal AI.</p>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>The Problem & Solution</h2>
            <p>Traditional mobile malware analysis relies heavily on sifting through dense network logs, making it incredibly difficult to catch <strong>UI Deception</strong> and <strong>Credential Harvesting</strong>. For example, a "Flashlight" app that renders a perfect fake Apple ID login prompt might bypass legacy scanners.</p>
            <p><strong>Jailbreak</strong> solves this by utilizing Google's Gemini 2.5 Flash AI model. It cross-references an application's visual UI (via sandbox screenshots) directly against its stated developer intent. If a basic calculator asks for banking credentials, the AI catches the behavioral mismatch and dynamically flags the threat.</p>
            
            <div class="tech-stack">
                <span class="badge">Python</span>
                <span class="badge">FastAPI</span>
                <span class="badge">Google GenAI</span>
                <span class="badge">JavaScript</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>System Architecture</h2>
            <p>The architecture flows from a local JS dashboard, piping a Multimodal Payload (Image + User Intent) through a secure FastAPI backend, and straight into the LLM for strict JSON classification.</p>
            
            <img src="images/jailbreak-systemArch.png" 
                 alt="Jailbreak Multimodal AI Sequence Diagram"
                 style="width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; margin-top: 20px;">
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2>Live Demonstration</h2>
            <p>Watch the AI dynamically analyze a secure app's intent versus a credential-harvesting phishing attempt.</p>
            
